  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> roughly</p><p>Top, tail, peel and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Bash your <strong>coconut</strong> <strong>flakes</strong> in their bag with a <strong>rolling</strong> <strong>pin </strong>(keep them in the bag so you don’t lose any!)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1688730524165-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1688730524165-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1688730524165-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1688730524165-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1688730524165-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Strip your <strong>mint</strong> <strong>leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them finely, discard the stems</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1688730528515-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1688730528515-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1688730528515-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1688730528515-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1688730528515-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>tomato paste </strong>in 175ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[230ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1688730532441-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1688730532441-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1688730532441-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1688730532441-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1688730532441-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat, once hot, add your <strong>coconut flakes</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don’t burn!</p><p>Once toasted, transfer the <strong>toasted coconut flakes </strong>to a bowl, reserve the pan</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped mint</strong> to the bowl and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>coconut crumb</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1688730536005-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1688730536005-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1688730536005-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1688730536005-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1688730536005-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati</strong> <strong>rice</strong> and <strong>grated</strong> <strong>carrot</strong> to a pot with a lid with 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[320ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat, mix through your <strong>chopped dates</strong> and keep covered until serving – this is your<strong> date rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1688730540462-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1688730540462-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1688730540462-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1688730540462-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1688730540462-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> with your<strong> chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>garam</strong> <strong>masala</strong> and <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong></p><p>Cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1688730544734-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1688730544734-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1688730544734-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1688730544734-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1688730544734-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>tomato</strong> to the pan with the <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>stock</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 4-5 min or until thickened</p><p>Once thickened, drain, then add your <strong>king</strong> <strong>prawns</strong> and cook for a further 4-5 min or until cooked through – this is your <strong>mild king prawn curry</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1688730548907-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1688730548907-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1688730548907-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1688730548907-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1688730548907-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>mild king prawn curry</strong> over the <strong>date</strong> <strong>rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>coconut crumb</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave out the coconut crumb!</span></strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
